<div class="recipe-detail">

  <div class="recipe-main">
    <h1 class="recipe-heading"><%= @recipe.name %></h1>
    <p class="recipe-description mod-detail"><%= @recipe.description %></p>

    <h2>Instructions</h2>

    <ol class="recipe-steps">
    <%= for {step, idx} <- Enum.with_index @recipe.steps do %>
      <li class="recipe-step-item">
        <p class="recipe-step-number">Step <%= idx + 1 %></p>
        <p class="recipe-step-text"><%= step %></p>
      </li>

    <% end %>
    </ol>

    <%# <ol class="recipe-steps">
      <li class="recipe-step-item">
        <p class="recipe-step-number">Step 1</p>
        <p class="recipe-step-text">Dissolve the yeast into 300g of room temperature water.</p>
      </li>

      <li class="recipe-step-item">
        <p class="recipe-step-number">Step 2</p>
        <p class="recipe-step-text">Put the flour into a tub or bowl. Slowly incorporate the yeast water. The dough should come together and look like a traditional biga. Cover and leave at room temperature for around 13 hours. Make sure it doesn't dry out.
        </p>
      </li>

      <li class="recipe-step-item">
        <p class="recipe-step-number">Step 3</p>
        <p class="recipe-step-text">Open the San Marzano tomatoes. Put them through a food mill to remove the seeds and skin. Add Salt and a pinch of oregano to taste. Store in the refrigerator until later.</p>
      </li>

      <li class="recipe-step-item">
        <p class="recipe-step-number">Step 4</p>
        <p class="recipe-step-text">With an electric whisk or a mixer slowly add 120g of chilled water. Once this has been added. Add the salt and mix for 30 seconds. Add the oil and mix for another 30 seconds.</p>
      </li>

      <li class="recipe-step-item">
        <p class="recipe-step-number">Step 5</p>
        <p class="recipe-step-text">Split the dough into 4 equal pieces of around 260g. Ball these and allow to double in size, this should take around 2 hours. Take your tomato sauce out of the fridge and allow it to warm to room temperature.
        </p>
      </li>

      <li class="recipe-step-item">
        <p class="recipe-step-number">Step 6</p>
        <p class="recipe-step-text">Stretch the dough out. Add the tomato sauce and mozzarella and you're ready to bake.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol> %>
  </div>


  <div class="recipe-overview">
    <div class="recipe-overview-section">
      <h2>Recipe Overview</h2>

      <p>🍕 <%= @recipe.number_of_pizzas %> pizzas</p>
      <p>⏲ <%= @recipe.duration %> hours</p>
      <p>🔥 <%= @recipe.oven_type |> Atom.to_string |> String.capitalize %> Oven</p>
      <p>💧 70% Hydration</p>
    </div>


    <div class="recipe-overview-section">
      <h2>Ingredients</h2>

      <p>💧 420g of water</p>
      <p>🥨 600g Caputo 00</p>
      <p>🍅 400g tin of San Marzano</p>
      <p>🧂 12g Salt</p>
      <p>🥯 6g Fresh Yeast</p>
      <p>🛢 6g of Olive Oil<p>
      <p>🧀 Handful of Buffalo Mozzeralla</p>
      <p>🍃 Handful of Basil</p>
    </div>

    <div class="recipe-overview-section">
      <h2>Equipment</h2>

      Ooni Koda 16
    </div>

  </div>
</div>

<h2>Pictures</h2>

<%= render_recipe_images(@conn, @recipe) %>
</div>
